<title>Functions and Testing</title>


<introduction>
<p>
So far, we've written programs that have only one function, named <c>main</c>.
In this chapter, we'll show you how to organize programs into multiple functions.
We'll also take a look at the <c>Math</c> class, which provides functions for common mathematical operations.
Finally, we'll discuss strategies for incrementally developing and testing your code.
</p>
